      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo hemolysis index validation — full operating envelope",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. Monte Carlo sampling (n=500) applied to inlet velocity and viscosity distributions. Aggregate normalized index error mean 18.3%, exceeding the 10% acceptance threshold at MRL 5. Aleatory uncertainty in blood rheology and pump manufacturing tolerances discussed in the uncertainty narrative but no formal UQ artifact is linked to this result.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/mc-hemolysis-fullfield-500"
    },
    {
