      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Peak wall-shear stress validation at design point",
      "description": "Comparison of CFD peak wall-shear stress against PIV measurements at the nominal VAD design point (5 L/min, 3000 RPM). Relative error 12.4% against experimental mean. Uncertainty in experimental measurement repeatability is acknowledged in the body of the credibility report (section 4.3) but no structured UQ artifact is attached to this validation result. Aleatory variability in blood analog viscosity across test runs contributes an estimated ±6% band per laboratory log, yet this band is not formally linked here."
